The trees: 
 can provide shelter for the hens; 
 make the area less attractive for water birds and waders, which are 
known to be risk birds for avian influenza;  
 can reduce point load of nutrients because hens spread over a larger 
surface;  
 will increase carbon storage; 
 (in the green season) may capture dust from the poultry house, and 
 their management and the harvest are a diversification of the labour 
for (care) workers on the farm.
